                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.61334/135: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bading</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-22T16:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1924—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Department’s telegram 16, September 16, noon. I have received direct
                    assurance from the President that the Mercantile Bank matter will be arranged
                    satisfactorily. The President favors last year’s bill providing for liquidation
                    of the Association and continuation of tax, and is opposed to budget article
                    providing for denial of obligation of the state after December 31st, 1925.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bading</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
